Difference Between Static Method and Instance Method
Feature	Static Method	Instance Method
Belongs To	Class	Object
Keyword	static used	No static
Object Required?	âŒ No	âœ… Yes
Can Access Static Variables?	âœ… Yes	âœ… Yes
Can Access Instance Variables Directly?	âŒ No	âœ… Yes
Memory	Only one copy	Each object has access
ğŸ”¥ 1ï¸âƒ£ Static Method
Definition:

A method declared using static keyword.

Example:
class Test {
    static int cube(int n) {
        return n * n * n;
    }
}

Calling:
System.out.println(Test.cube(3));


ğŸ‘‰ No object needed.

ğŸ”¥ 2ï¸âƒ£ Instance Method
Definition:

A method without static keyword.

Example:
class Test {
    public void msg() {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}

Calling:
Test obj = new Test();
obj.msg();


ğŸ‘‰ Object is required.

ğŸ”¥ Why Static Method Cannot Access Instance Variables Directly?

Example:

class Demo {
    int x = 10;       // instance variable
    static int y = 20; // static variable

    static void show() {
        System.out.println(y); // âœ… allowed
        System.out.println(x); // âŒ ERROR
    }
}

Why error?

Because:

x belongs to object

But static method runs without object

So no object â†’ no instance variable access

ğŸ”¥ Instance Method Can Access Both
class Demo {
    int x = 10;
    static int y = 20;

    void display() {
        System.out.println(x); // âœ…
        System.out.println(y); // âœ…
    }
}


Because instance method runs with object.

ğŸ¯ Real Life Example

Think:

Class = College
Static method = College rules (same for all)
Instance method = Student behavior (different per student)

ğŸ”¥ Interview One-Line Answer

â€œStatic method belongs to class and can be called without object, while instance method belongs to object and requires object to be called.â€

âš¡ Important Extra Points (Interview Level)

Static method cannot be overridden (only hidden).

Instance method can be overridden.

main() is static method.
